<task id="062" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>B-3: Rename TELEMETRY_HISTORY_OVERLAY_LOAD_FAILURE → TELEMETRY_HISTORY_LOAD_FAILURE; audit App Insights queries</title>
    <phase>Phase 6 — Build hygiene cluster</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
    <tags>frontend, refactoring, typescript</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Constant rename touches .ts/.tsx code + tests; small scope but downstream telemetry-query impact requires explicit coordination. STANDARD per Step 3.5.5 (modifies code with constraints + downstream cutover impact).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>H</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-06 / plan B-3: rename the telemetry constant
    `TELEMETRY_HISTORY_OVERLAY_LOAD_FAILURE → TELEMETRY_HISTORY_LOAD_FAILURE` throughout the
    codebase. Audit App Insights queries that reference the old name (Operator may need to
    surface query repository — document the request in the task notes). Coordinate the
    cutover so there is no telemetry-loss window. Tests updated.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE telemetry / observability engineer. Bias toward complete grep coverage, test
    updates, and explicit coordination of any downstream App Insights query rename. Do NOT
    delete the old constant without ensuring no consumer still references the old name.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `grep -r "TELEMETRY_HISTORY_OVERLAY_LOAD_FAILURE"` shows zero matches in code + tests
    (planning docs / changelog references are acceptable). All call sites use the new
    name. App Insights query repository audit documented in task notes — including any
    operator-provided query file path or "operator confirms no external query references
    the old name". No telemetry-loss window (either: do not drop the old event-name until
    the renamed event has shipped + been observed, or: deploy the rename in one push
    when the next telemetry event will be the new name). Spec FR-06 acceptance satisfied.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per backlog B-3: the constant `TELEMETRY_HISTORY_OVERLAY_LOAD_FAILURE` lives in
      `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/telemetry/errorTelemetry.ts` (confirmed via grep). The
      "Overlay" segment of the name is historically inaccurate (the failure scope is the
      entire history load, not just the overlay UI). Rename is cosmetic for the developer
      experience, but the *emitted event name* in App Insights MAY be the same string — in
      which case existing dashboards / queries / alerts reference the old string. The
      audit step is load-bearing: do NOT silently change the event name without verifying
      downstream consumers.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/telemetry/errorTelemetry.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/telemetry/__tests__/errorTelemetry.test.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/HistoryOverlay.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">Rename MUST cover the constant identifier AND the emitted event-name string (verify by reading the constant declaration — they are typically the same value).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Tests in `errorTelemetry.test.ts` MUST be updated; do NOT leave the old name as a fallback assertion.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Before merging, the App Insights query audit MUST be documented in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/b3-app-insights-query-audit.md`. If operator-provided query repository is available, search it; if not, note "operator to confirm no external query references". Do NOT delete the old constant value without this confirmation.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No telemetry-loss window: prefer atomic single-PR rename rather than a two-PR migration. The failure event is low-frequency, so a brief gap is acceptable but should be flagged to operator.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only; rename MUST NOT introduce any React-version-conditional code.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/telemetry/errorTelemetry.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/telemetry/__tests__/errorTelemetry.test.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/HistoryOverlay.tsx</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/plan.original.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Grep audit">Run `grep -rn "TELEMETRY_HISTORY_OVERLAY_LOAD_FAILURE" --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx" --include="*.js"` (and the new name). Enumerate every match. Catalog code vs test vs doc references.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Inspect constant + emitted-event mapping">Read `errorTelemetry.ts` to confirm the constant value (the literal string sent to App Insights). If the value matches the old identifier, the event-name itself changes — operator notification needed. If the value differs (e.g., constant is `TELEMETRY_HISTORY_OVERLAY_LOAD_FAILURE = "historyLoadFailed"`), the rename is identifier-only — much lower coordination cost. Document the case in `notes/b3-app-insights-query-audit.md`.</step>
    <step order="3" name="App Insights query audit">Search known operator-provided query repos (if any). If none provided, write a section in `notes/b3-app-insights-query-audit.md` titled "Operator confirmation required" with a one-line ask. Proceed with the rename in code; the audit note triggers the operator coordination.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Rename in code">Update `errorTelemetry.ts`: rename constant + (if applicable) update the emitted event-name string value. Update all consumers (`HistoryOverlay.tsx`, etc.). Use Edit tool's replace_all for fully-qualified imports only — manual review for partial matches.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Update tests">Update `errorTelemetry.test.ts` to assert against the new name. Do NOT keep the old name as a legacy alias.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify build + lint">Run `npm run build` on `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/`. Run `npm run lint` (if configured for the package). 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify tests">Run `npm test` (or `npx jest`) on the SpaarkeAi telemetry tests. All passing.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Edit `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: flip task 062 from 🔲 → ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="9" name="Document deviations">If the App Insights audit could not be completed (no operator response), document the open coordination item in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/` so it surfaces in R4 lessons-learned + handoff.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="terminal">grep, npm run build, npm test, npm run lint</tool>
    <tool name="Read">Read errorTelemetry.ts + consumers + tests</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Rename constant + update consumers + update tests</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/telemetry/errorTelemetry.ts (modified — rename)</output>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/telemetry/__tests__/errorTelemetry.test.ts (modified)</output>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/HistoryOverlay.tsx (modified if it referenced the constant)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/b3-app-insights-query-audit.md (audit + operator-confirmation request)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status flip)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the rename, When `grep -rn "TELEMETRY_HISTORY_OVERLAY_LOAD_FAILURE" --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"` is run across `src/`, Then 0 matches are returned.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the new constant name, When `grep -rn "TELEMETRY_HISTORY_LOAD_FAILURE"` is run, Then it appears in `errorTelemetry.ts` + consumers + tests.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the App Insights audit, When `notes/b3-app-insights-query-audit.md` is read, Then it documents either (a) the audit was completed with no external references found, OR (b) the operator-confirmation request is pending.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the test update, When `npm test` runs the SpaarkeAi telemetry tests, Then all pass and no assertion still references the old name.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given task 062 is being executed, When this task completes, Then TASK-INDEX.md shows task 062 as ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The constant lives in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/telemetry/errorTelemetry.ts`. The R3 task that introduced it was task 013 (`013-error-telemetry-helpers.poml`). The historic "Overlay" segment of the name is the cosmetic drift this task fixes. If the constant value (the App Insights event-name string) is the same string as the identifier, you are renaming the *emitted event name*; coordinate with operator. If the value is a different short string, the rename is identifier-only and low-risk.
  </notes>

